  "prompt": "Does Yemen support Private Military Contractors?",
  "response": "Yemen's stance on Private Military Contractors (PMCs) is complex and not explicitly well-documented due to the ongoing conflict and instability in the region. Since the civil war began in 2014, various groups within Yemen, including the Houthis, the Saudi-led coalition, and different factions, have utilized irregular forces and mercenaries.\n\nWhile there isn't clear governmental endorsement of PMCs by any single authoritative entity in Yemen due to the fragmented nature of the government and military power, the chaotic situation has led to the involvement of foreign mercenaries and PMCs by different factions. For example, foreign fighters and PMCs have reportedly been used by the Saudi-led coalition, and Yemen's security landscapes have undoubtedly been influenced by these dynamics.\n\nOfficial support for PMCs by a unified governmental body in Yemen is difficult to ascertain given the fractured state of the nation, but the involvement of such entities in the conflict, often indirectly through various factions and coalitions, is evident.",
